Choose the operating system  
  

To provide a cloud dedicated server service, we use AMD EPYC 7742 processors
with a frequency of 2.25GHz - 3.4GHz, DDR-4 3200MHz ECC Reg server RAM,
Samsung SM professional server NVMe SSD drives, as well as server platforms of
the best brands.  
  

What equipment do you use to provide services?

The cloud virtual VPS service does not imply the allocation of certain
processor cores to the client. All server processing power is shared and
distributed among all clients. At the same time, we do not allow server
overloads. There are certain restrictions on these tariffs: when the processor
is utilized, more than 60% on average daily, you will be asked to switch to
the next tariff, or transfer your service to the Cloud Dedicated Server VDS
cluster.  
For comparison, the “Cloud Dedicated Server VDS” service has certain processor
cores allocated to each client. RAM, disk space does not overlap with other
clients. Due to this, the speed of your tasks is ensured in comparison with
the more budgetary cloud virtual VPS server.

What is the difference between a cloud virtual VPS server and a cloud
dedicated VDS server?

You can pay for services with bank cards issued all over the world: VISA,
Mastercard, MIR, AMEX (“PayPal / bank cards Euro” payment method). Services
can also be paid for:  

  * By bank transfer in euro from a legal entity abroad, we provide Invoice.
  * By bank transfer in rubles from a legal entity of the Russian Federation, we provide all closing documents.
  * Cryptocurrencies through the CoinPayments system when passing through personal identification.

With a cloud dedicated server, we provide the VMManager control panel for
free, in which you can access the server's VNC console, reinstall the OS,
reboot the server, view resource utilization statistics, as well as upload
your own ISO image and install your operating system.  
  

Is the server control panel included in the price?

We do not provide a trial period, but we do have a refund of the balance.

The cost of the server includes 1 IPv4 address, as well as a /64 IPv6 network.
You can order additional IPv4 addresses, the cost is 2 euros per month for
each additional IPv4 address.

How many IP addresses are provided with the server? Can I order an additional
IP address?

When ordering Windows OS, you can connect to the server using RDP (Remote
Desktop Connection). When ordering a Unix like OS, you get root SSH access.

How can I connect to the server?

With each server 30TB of traffic is included in the price. Exceeding this
volume is charged at a rate of 2 euros per 1TB. If you need unlimited traffic,
use the “Cloud Dedicated Server VDS” service.

How much traffic is included?

We do not provide system administration services. The cost of the service
includes only computing resources.

Is system administration included in the cost of services?
